ISDA does not assume any responsibility for any use to which this document may be put. Each party must satisfy itself as to the effectiveness and appropriateness of this document and ensure it is used and/or adapted to reflect the commercial intentions and legal and regulatory obligations of the parties.  Parties should seek legal, tax and accounting advice and consult with any other adviser they deem appropriate prior to using this document.

ISDA has not undertaken to review any applicable laws and regulations of any jurisdiction in which this document may be used or of any jurisdiction whose laws or regulations affect derivative contracts, indices, securities and/or currencies that may be the subject of a privately negotiated derivative transaction.  Parties are therefore advised to consider the application of any relevant jurisdiction’s legal, regulatory, tax, accounting, exchange or other requirements that may exist in connection with using this document.

MA02_SET_OFF.textAmendment:
Amendments to Set-Off. Section 6(f) of this Agreement is hereby deleted in its entirety.

Amendments to Set-Off. Section 6(f) of this Agreement is hereby amended by replacing the words “payable by the Payee to the Payer” with the words “payable by the Payee (or any Affiliate of X if X is the Payee) to the Payor (or any Affiliate of X if X is the Payor)”.

Amendments to Set-Off. Section 6(f) shall be deleted in its entirety and replaced with the following Section 6(f):

“(f) Set-Off. Upon [the designation of an Early Termination Date]/ [the occurrence of an Event of Default or Termination Event in respect of which all Transactions are Affected Transactions and there is a sole Affected Party], the Non-defaulting Party or the Non-affected Party (in each case, “X”) shall have the right, but not the obligation, without prior notice to the Defaulting Party or Affected Party (“Y”) to set-off or apply any amounts or obligations (whether or not arising under this Agreement, whether or not matured, whether actual or contingent and irrespective of currency, place of payment or booking office) owed by Y to X or any Affiliate of X against any amounts or obligations (whether or not arising under this Agreement, whether or not matured, whether actual or contingent and irrespective of currency, place of payment or booking office) owed by X or any Affiliate of X to Y. X shall give notice to Y of any set-off effected under this Section 6(f), provided that any failure to give such notice shall not invalidate the relevant set-off.

For this purpose, any amount (or the relevant portion of such amounts) subject to set-off may be converted by X into the currency in which the other is denominated at the rate of exchange at which such party would be able, acting in good faith and using commercially reasonable procedures, to purchase the relevant amount of such currency.

If an obligation is unascertained, X may in good faith estimate that obligation and set off in respect of the estimate, subject to the relevant party accounting to the other when the obligation is ascertained.

Nothing in this Section 6(f) will be effective to create a charge or other security interest. This Section 6(f) will be without prejudice and in addition to any right of set-off, offset, combination of accounts, lien, right of retention or withholding or similar right or requirement to which any party is at any time otherwise entitled or subject (whether by operation of law, contract or otherwise).”

MA02_FXTCO_V6.textAmendment:
Failure to Pay Premium on the Premium Payment Date. Article 3, Section 3.4 of the 1998 FX Definitions is hereby amended by the additions of the following as a new paragraph (c) of the 1998 FX and Currency Option Definitions as published by the International Swaps and Derivatives Association Inc, the Emerging Markets Traders Association and the Foreign Exchange Committee, as amended or supplemented from time to time.

"(c) Premium: Failure to Pay on Premium Payment Date. If any Premium is not received on the Premium Payment Date, the Seller may elect: (i) to accept a late payment of such Premium; (ii) to give written notice of such non-payment and, if such payment is not received within two (2) Local Business Days of such notice, treat the related Currency Option as void; or (iii) to give written notice of such non-payment and, if such payment shall not be received within two (2) Local Business Days of such notice, treat such non-payment as an Event of Default under Section 5(a)(i). If the Seller elects to act under either clause (i) or (ii) of the preceding sentence the Buyer shall pay all out-of-pocket costs and actual damages including, without limitation, interest on such Premium in the same currency as such Premium at the then prevailing market rate and any other costs or expenses incurred by the Seller in covering its obligations (including, without limitation, a delta hedge) with respect to such Currency Option.”

MA02_FXTCO_V1.textAmendment:
Expanding the Scope of Transactions Governed by the Agreement to Include All FX and Currency Option Transactions. Any transaction outstanding between the parties on the date this Agreement comes into force, or entered into between the parties on or after the date of this Agreement, that is an FX Transaction or a Currency Option Transaction (as each such term is defined in the 1998 FX and Currency Option Definitions as published by the International Swaps and Derivatives Association Inc, the Emerging Markets Traders Association and the Foreign Exchange Committee, as amended or supplemented from time to time (the “FX Definitions”)), will, unless otherwise specifically stated in the relevant Confirmation, constitute a “Transaction” for the purposes of this Agreement and such confirmation shall constitute a Confirmation. Where a Foreign Exchange Transaction or Currency Option Transaction (as each such term is defined in the FX Definitions) is confirmed by means of exchange of electronic message on an electronic messaging system or other document or other confirming evidence exchanged between the parties confirming such Transaction, such messages, document or other evidence will constitute a Confirmation under this Agreement even if not so specified therein.

Source of Forms of Confirmation. Each Confirmation shall be substantially in the form of [one of the Exhibits to the 2000 ISDA Definitions or in any other form which is published by the International Swaps and Derivatives Association, Inc. or in such other form as the parties may agree]/[one of the Exhibits to the 2006 ISDA Definitions or in any other form which is published by the International Swaps and Derivatives Association, Inc. or in such other form as the parties may agree]/[Exhibit A hereto]/[_].

Confirmation Procedures. For each Transaction that Party A and Party B enter hereunder, [Party A]/[Party B] shall promptly send to [Party A]/[Party B] a Confirmation setting forth the terms of such Transaction and [Party A]/[Party B] shall execute and return the Confirmation to [Party A]/[Party B] within [a commercially reasonably time]/[_].

MA02_SET_OFF.textAmendment:
Amendments to Set-Off. Section 6(f) of this Agreement is hereby deleted in its entirety.

Amendments to Set-Off. Section 6(f) of this Agreement is hereby amended by replacing the words “payable by the Payee to the Payer” with the words “payable by the Payee (or any Affiliate of X if X is the Payee) to the Payor (or any Affiliate of X if X is the Payor)”.

Amendments to Set-Off. Section 6(f) shall be deleted in its entirety and replaced with the following Section 6(f):

“(f) Set-Off. Upon [the designation of an Early Termination Date]/ [the occurrence of an Event of Default or Termination Event in respect of which all Transactions are Affected Transactions and there is a sole Affected Party], the Non-defaulting Party or the Non-affected Party (in each case, “X”) shall have the right, but not the obligation, without prior notice to the Defaulting Party or Affected Party (“Y”) to set-off or apply any amounts or obligations (whether or not arising under this Agreement, whether or not matured, whether actual or contingent and irrespective of currency, place of payment or booking office) owed by Y to X or any Affiliate of X against any amounts or obligations (whether or not arising under this Agreement, whether or not matured, whether actual or contingent and irrespective of currency, place of payment or booking office) owed by X or any Affiliate of X to Y. X shall give notice to Y of any set-off effected under this Section 6(f), provided that any failure to give such notice shall not invalidate the relevant set-off.

For this purpose, any amount (or the relevant portion of such amounts) subject to set-off may be converted by X into the currency in which the other is denominated at the rate of exchange at which such party would be able, acting in good faith and using commercially reasonable procedures, to purchase the relevant amount of such currency.

If an obligation is unascertained, X may in good faith estimate that obligation and set off in respect of the estimate, subject to the relevant party accounting to the other when the obligation is ascertained.

Nothing in this Section 6(f) will be effective to create a charge or other security interest. This Section 6(f) will be without prejudice and in addition to any right of set-off, offset, combination of accounts, lien, right of retention or withholding or similar right or requirement to which any party is at any time otherwise entitled or subject (whether by operation of law, contract or otherwise).”

MA02_FXTCO_V6.textAmendment:
Failure to Pay Premium on the Premium Payment Date. Article 3, Section 3.4 of the 1998 FX Definitions is hereby amended by the additions of the following as a new paragraph (c) of the 1998 FX and Currency Option Definitions as published by the International Swaps and Derivatives Association Inc, the Emerging Markets Traders Association and the Foreign Exchange Committee, as amended or supplemented from time to time.

"(c) Premium: Failure to Pay on Premium Payment Date. If any Premium is not received on the Premium Payment Date, the Seller may elect: (i) to accept a late payment of such Premium; (ii) to give written notice of such non-payment and, if such payment is not received within two (2) Local Business Days of such notice, treat the related Currency Option as void; or (iii) to give written notice of such non-payment and, if such payment shall not be received within two (2) Local Business Days of such notice, treat such non-payment as an Event of Default under Section 5(a)(i). If the Seller elects to act under either clause (i) or (ii) of the preceding sentence the Buyer shall pay all out-of-pocket costs and actual damages including, without limitation, interest on such Premium in the same currency as such Premium at the then prevailing market rate and any other costs or expenses incurred by the Seller in covering its obligations (including, without limitation, a delta hedge) with respect to such Currency Option.”

MA02_FXTCO_V1.textAmendment:
Expanding the Scope of Transactions Governed by the Agreement to Include All FX and Currency Option Transactions. Any transaction outstanding between the parties on the date this Agreement comes into force, or entered into between the parties on or after the date of this Agreement, that is an FX Transaction or a Currency Option Transaction (as each such term is defined in the 1998 FX and Currency Option Definitions as published by the International Swaps and Derivatives Association Inc, the Emerging Markets Traders Association and the Foreign Exchange Committee, as amended or supplemented from time to time (the “FX Definitions”)), will, unless otherwise specifically stated in the relevant Confirmation, constitute a “Transaction” for the purposes of this Agreement and such confirmation shall constitute a Confirmation. Where a Foreign Exchange Transaction or Currency Option Transaction (as each such term is defined in the FX Definitions) is confirmed by means of exchange of electronic message on an electronic messaging system or other document or other confirming evidence exchanged between the parties confirming such Transaction, such messages, document or other evidence will constitute a Confirmation under this Agreement even if not so specified therein.
